on zabbix UI:
export HP_array.2014.01.14.xml template

on all servers with HP array (copy hparray dir to servers):
1.
for CentOS (if you have another Linux OS use aptitude and etc)
find in Internet hpacucli-9.40-12.0.i386.rpm or latest version 
install it (rpm -ivh /root/hpacucli-9.40-12.0.i386.rpm) (if you have 64bit: yum install glibc.i686 libgcc.i686 libstdc++.i686 )

2. file hparray/userparams_hparry.conf
by default I use /usr/local/zabbix for zabbix (maybe need change it to /etc/zabbix)

3.
hparray/zabbixhparraycrontab
by default I use /usr/local/zabbix for zabbix (maybe need change it to /etc/zabbix)

4.
copy hparray dir to your zabbix etc dir

cp hparray /usr/local/zabbix/etc
or
cp hparray /etc/zabbix

5.
cd /usr/local/zabbix/etc/mapr 
(or /etc/zabbix/mapr) 

ln -s zabbixhparraycrontab /etc/cron.d/
ln -s userparams_hparry.conf /usr/local/zabbix/etc/zabbix_agentd.conf.d/
or
ln -s userparams_hparry.conf /etc/zabbix/zabbix_agentd.conf.d/

7. 
reload cron (/etc/init.d/crond reload)
reload zabbix_agentd (/etc/init.d/zabbix_agentd reload or /etc/init.d/zabbix-agentd reload or etc)
